{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"be348c9e-60ef-4025-beba-da7d16217782","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2**, which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    // Inject TestContext via constructor (MSTest v3+)\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous initialization here\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization — runs before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // await async setup work\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SyncTest() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task AsyncTest() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — use for sync init and receiving `TestContext` via DI (MSTest v3+).\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — use for `async` setup (`Task`-returning method).\n- Avoid the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property-injection pattern; constructor injection is preferred in modern MSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"333fe5ae-05c6-4b9c-9f40-39befccdce95","outputTokens":276,"requestId":"CFC7:2E7D56:14E86CF:184EEE2:69EC1720"},"id":"e22f09a3-8ec4-45a2-8401-71117dc042c5","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:21:43.188Z","parentId":"81a15550-85a2-44aa-877a-9b7780a1eca6"}
